        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 4:14PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 414 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 14 miles north of Santa Rosa Lake State
Park to over Pastura, moving southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Rosa, Santa Rosa Lake State Park, Colonias and Pastura.

This includes Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 256 and 284.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
